{{Coord|72|2|S|14|35|E|display=title|type:mountain}} The '''Payer Mountains''' is a group of scattered [[mountain]]s extending north-south for about {{convert|23|mi|km}}, standing {{convert|10|mi|km}} east of the [[Weyprecht Mountains]] and forming the eastern half of the [[Hoel Mountains]] in central [[Queen Maud Land]]. They were discovered by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938â1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]], and named for [[Julius Payer]], [[Austria]]n [[polar explorer]], who in company with [[Karl Weyprecht]] discovered [[Franz Josef Land]] in 1873.<ref>[http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/ USGS GNIS: Payer Mountains]</ref>
